Modified Page Writer : Background kernel threads monitor te modified list. When this list gets too long, these threads wake up to flush the dirty pages to the pagefile. 
To create the PFN, i suggest to use an API for devices to fetch pages from the MMU, each time that API is called a handle is given to the MMU to establish the page sharing and the new connected device 
is updated to the database. 
When a CPU process uses a page, the OS can swap that page to the disk whenever it wants. A hardware device doesnt understand page fault. If the OS pages out a memory block while a device is mid write the device will
write data into a physical frame that might now belong to a different process. You must pin or Lock the page using MmProbeAndLockPages. A user-mode app asks a device to write data into buffer A. The kernel moves the 
data in buffer A to the Pagefile on idsk and marks that physical RAM frame as free. The kernel gives that same physical RAM frame to a different process to store a password. The NVMe drive unaware of the OS's internal bo
okkepping writes data to that physical address and overwrite the browser memory's process.   
